## ğŸ“– Part 2: Optimizing Website Performance  

ğŸ¯ **Fast websites rank better and provide a better user experience.**  

ğŸ”¹ **1. Minify CSS & JavaScript (Reduce File Sizes)**  
- Use **minified CSS & JS files** (`style.min.css`, `script.min.js`).  
- Example: [CSS Minifier](https://cssminifier.com/)  

ğŸ”¹ **2. Optimize Images**  
- Use **compressed formats** (`WebP`, `JPEG`, `SVG`).  
- Example: [TinyPNG](https://tinypng.com/)  

```css
img {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}
```

ğŸ”¹ **3. Enable Lazy Loading for Images**  
```html
<img src="image.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="Optimized Image">
```

ğŸ”¹ **4. Use a Content Delivery Network (CDN)**  
- Example: **Cloudflare, Fastly, or BunnyCDN** to **serve content faster globally**.  

ğŸ¯ **Bonus:** Use **Google PageSpeed Insights** ([https://pagespeed.web.dev/](https://pagespeed.web.dev/)) to test performance!  

