## ğŸ“– Part 5: Website Security Best Practices  

ğŸ“Œ **Keep your website secure with these tips:**  
âœ… **Use HTTPS (SSL Certificate)** â€“ Encrypts data & improves SEO.  
âœ… **Validate User Input** â€“ Prevents **XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) attacks**.  
âœ… **Use Strong Passwords** â€“ Protects website admin areas.  
âœ… **Keep Your Code Updated** â€“ Fixes security bugs.  

ğŸ”¹ **Example: Force HTTPS in HTML (`.htaccess` for Apache Hosting)**  
```apache
RewriteEngine On
RewriteCond %{HTTPS} off
RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [L,R=301]
```

ğŸ¯ **Bonus:** Scan your website for security risks using **Mozilla Observatory** ([https://observatory.mozilla.org/](https://observatory.mozilla.org/))!  

